<header class="slide-title">
  <h1 class="title">
    <span class="title-main">{{text.title.main}}</span>
    <span class="title-sub">{{text.title.sub}}</span>
  </h1>
  <h2 class="subtitle">{{text.subtitle}}</h2>
  <date class="date">{{text.data}}</date>
  <ul class="authors">
    <li><a href="{{text.author.url}}">{{text.author.name}}</a></li>
    <li>with</li>
    <li><a href="{{text.advisor.url}}">{{text.advisor.name}}</a></li>
  </ul>
  <div class="marks">
    <img src="DIGEST(/images/tmdsc/tmd-crystal-top.png)"
         alt="TMD crystal">
    <img src="DIGEST(/images/ucr-logo-white.svg)"
         alt="{{text.ucr.name}}">
  </div>
</header>

<section class="slide-background">
  <h2>Background</h2>
  <div class="background-2d">
    <figure class="fig-graphene">
      <figcaption>
        By AlexanderAlUS (Own work)
        [<a href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0">CC BY-SA 3.0
        </a>
        or
        <a href="http://www.gnu.org/copyleft/fdl.html">GFDL</a>],
        <a href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File%3AGraphen.jpg">
          via Wikimedia Commons
        </a>
      </figcaption>
      <img src="DIGEST(/images/graphene.jpg" alt="">
    </figure>
    <div>
      <h3>2D Materials promise novel application</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Graphene discovered 2004</li>
        <li>Unique properties from the bulk</li>
        <li>Hexagonal lattice, high electron mobility</li>
        <li>Relativistic low-energy model: Dirac cones, linear dispersion</li>
        <li>Monolayer TMDs: hexagonal lattice</li>
        <li>Gapped with strong spin-orbit coupling</li>
        <li>Strong, flexible &amp; transparent</li>
        <li>Both excellent candidates for spintronic devices</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  <div class="background-spin">
    <h3>Spintronics</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Nobel Prize for GMR in 2007</li>
      <li>A future with devices built on spin-current</li>
      <li>Smaller and lower power</li>
      <li>Need to find suitable materials</li>
      <li>Graphene? Predicted excellent conductor for spin-current</li>
      <li>TMDs? No spin degeneracy and spin couples to light polarization</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  </div>
</section>
